# Code Quality Standards

## Naming Conventions

- **Components**: PascalCase (`UserProfile`, `LoginForm`)
- **Variables/Functions**: camelCase (`userName`, `fetchData`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`API_URL`, `MAX_RETRIES`)
- **Types/Interfaces**: PascalCase (`UserData`, `ApiResponse`)
- **Files**: kebab-case or PascalCase for components ( `UserProfile.tsx`)

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Proper error handling
try {
  const data = await fetchData();
  return data;
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Failed to fetch data:', error);
  throw new Error('Data fetch failed', { cause: error });
}

// ❌ BAD - Silent failures
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {}
```

## Performance

- Use `React.memo()` for expensive components
- Lazy load routes: `const Page = lazy(() => import('./Page'))`
- Memoize expensive calculations with `useMemo()`
- Memoize callbacks with `useCallback()` when passed to child components

## Accessibility

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Semantic HTML and ARIA labels
<button aria-label="Close dialog" onClick={onClose}>
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
  <span className="sr-only">Close</span>
</button>

// Ensure keyboard navigation works
// Use semantic HTML (button, nav, header, main, etc.)
```
